snippet.title: The Hand That Spins The Vinyl
snippet.description: ​Lots of people think that when the devil lies to you, it involves a supremely ironic spin on the truth - like promising you'll become beautiful, only to turn you into a department store mannequin or something. Really though, Satan doesn't have time for any of that shit and his lies are fiercely economical and direct in nature - like promising you'll become beautiful, only to just not do that and go do something else instead.

snippet.title: The Lip Reader
snippet.description: Bobby "Blabbermouth" Feltoni knew there were spies in his midst. He couldn't trust the cops he paid off, couldn't trust his men, couldn't even trust his own wife. So he developed a language all his own, understandable only to him - a code of babbling he would slip into sometimes whenever he felt he was being watched. Therefore, none of his heists or whacks would ever wind up being successful (and one time, when he inadvertently sent his men into enemy territory down on Bab Bab Bab St., it would be disastrous), but at the same time he never did get caught.

snippet.title: How People Would Really Use Time Travel
snippet.description: Using time travel to inform your past self of where you left your car keys, or how bad the milk was, or that a guy peddling celebrity home tours is gonna bug you on the next street corner, is a really petty and meaningless use of time travel - particularly when you could be using it to stop Hitler or 9/11 or Pol Pot if you knew how to speak Khmer. So really, any interdimensional, organ-crushing time flux is on you, and fully deserved.

snippet.title: The Popular Girl's Graduation Speech
snippet.description: Becky Sanders went on to prove them all wrong. She not only raised her baby, she got a job at a Fortune 500 company, worked her ass off for recognition and respect, and got promoted to a six-figure-a-year job within three years, earning more than all of her classmates. However, her baby grew up to be a hateful little piece of shit, because her mom loved listening to late-period Bon Jovi.

snippet.title: On Closer Inspection
snippet.description: Her super baby wound up shooting laser beams out of its hands, decapitating the doctors cleanly and painlessly. When she told her baby that was overcompensating, he turned to her and said, "The world's smartest man poses no more threat to me than does its smartest termite."

snippet.title: Late Night Rendevous
snippet.description: Yes. Yes, boys. He came. He came into her fort. Her fort. That's what he did. He came into her fort. And they played fort games. And then he left. And you know what? He felt glad he could just have a bizarre platonic relationship for once. Felt more mature. Like he wasn't beholden to his sexual urges, but rather a meaningful desire to connect emotionally with people. Maybe you should come into a girl's fort sometime, it'll do you some good.
